race.comment: WEXFORD MISS (8) was in the money two starts back at Grafton but was unable to repeat the effort last time when seventh, beaten 8 lengths, at Gold Coast over 1800m. Beautifully placed and is sure to take plenty of stopping. MONARCH EXPRESS (3) comes here off a last-start fourth, beaten 3.5 lengths, over 1400m at this track. Worth plenty of thought. AIMA SUN (5) was beaten 3.5 lengths into seventh over 1350m at Ipswich at her latest appearance. Well placed to turn things around. SHANNON'S LEGACY (7) hasn't been far away in recent efforts and gets in well after the claim. Has to be kept safe.
